Hello
I am 30 years old.
I started cocaine at 20 years old.
I never took it every day, I wasn't super addicted.
I used to take 1 or 2 times a month at most, but for about 6 months or a year now I can't control myself when I drink alcohol.
Even though before I promised myself not to look for drugs, after 2 or 3 drinks I start to get hot and I tell myself "come on we only have one life, let's go" and it's impossible to control myself, too much desire to take some.
So there you have it, I know the problem is alcohol at the base but it's crazy impossible to stop, in family, with friends, for apero, etc.
Does anyone have this problem?
Thank you
Stop drinking and the problem will be solved.
One must sometimes force oneself to stop...
Have you at least talked to your family doctor about it?
Seeing an addict could do you good, especially to "evaluate" your consumption.
In fact, it's in the evening that it's harder to keep up mentally.
The day is going well.
Hello,
I am polite with a big alcohol problem.
I have been sober from alcohol for a few years, but I can't tell myself that I will never drink another drop of alcohol, even though I want to, maybe not enough willpower.
It happens to me sometimes because it's stronger than me and as soon as I start, I can't stop myself.
After that I sleep very badly and am sick the next day and especially I hate myself.
I am ashamed, of who I become when I drink and I suffer from it.
I can't drink normally.
I drink all my glasses dry.
Why do I have this relationship with alcohol when so many people manage to drink normally?
I haven't drunk in 10 days.
This weekend I am invited to a birthday party and I am very, very scared.
If you understand me, live the same thing or have passed the point, I take everything that can help me.
Thank you for reading and I await your responses.
amicably
Claude529
Hi,
Yeah, why?
Dl
But why? lol
Do you also ask yourself the same question?
especially don't be sorry!!
